shortDescription: The secondary entrance is heavily fortified with turrets and 'Mech elevators to the surface but it also contains an outside door console that Dr. Murad can hack using Tech Jeremiah's backdoor to disable their defenses. Once we shut down the base, the rebels will be able take it over and bring the Militia's resources to their side.
longDescription: Dr. Murad has her electronic gear ready, we'll need to defend the 'Mech until she shuts down the Niops Militia base.

objectiveList.title: Stay Alive Until Dr. Murad uses the Backdoor

dialogueContent.words: This is as close as I can safely drop you outside the range of the Militia defenses.
Commander, we'll need to get a visual on the console for the hack to work.
Understood Dr. Murad.
You can expect turrets directly guarding the entrance and the console. And those 'Mech elevators will start working soon until we get them offline.
We still have to get a lot closer with this 'Mech for that to work.
Understood, Doctor. Commander, it's time we do this.
Tech Barba just reached the inside and shut down the entire base.
About time, it was getting hairy out there against all those Star League 'Mechs.
The Militia commander has just surrended the entire facility - it worked!
So your revolution was successful? You're the boss man now?
Yes to the first, no to the second. Da-Ri hasn't conceded yet and we didn't do this to get power for ourselves.
And I've heard that story too many times before.
Enough, Yang. Dr. Murad, once you rejoin the Hysteria we can collect our pay and let the niopsters figure it out for now.
Dr. Murad, are you still operational? Dr. Murad, please respond!
I've located the console but they have changed the frequencies used for the codes. I will need to make several attempts to find the right one, otherwise the backdoor can't be exploited.
It's not working... all the frequencies are unresponsive. It looks as if it requires direct input on the console.
This wouldn't have happened if I was there on the ground.
And we just triggered all the alarms on this Castle Brian.
Remotely accessing the console isn't working - the system is different from what I was expecting. I may need to step outside...
You're staying inside! You can't go out there in the field now!
Look at the mountain sides! Those 'Mech lifts are about to open!
We can't stay here long - the Militia 'Mechs will overcome us eventually!
Now it's too risky to approach that console on foot with all the defenses about to become active - if only your doctor hadn't been so adamant...
No! I think I finally recognize the console model - there should be an additional infrared port but it will require line of sight with my 'Mech.
We don't have time for you to go through all the frequencies and you'll need to get closer.
I don't need to test all of them... all I need is to find the right one quickly...
I'm sorry to say this but with all the activity that is powering up down there, it will be impossible to try to exfiltrate them as this point.
The base turrets have just come online!
We can't stay here this long - the Militia 'Mechs will overcome us eventually!
Now it's too risky to approach that console on foot with all the defenses about to become active - if only your doctor hadn't been so adamant...
No! I think I finally recognize the console model - there should be an additional infrared port but it will require line of sight with my 'Mech.
We don't have time for you to go through all the frequencies and you'll need to get closer.
I don't need to test all of them... all I need is to find the right one quickly...
I'm sorry to say this but will all the activity that is powering up down there, it will be impossible to try to exfiltrate them as this point.
The base turrets have just become online!
[static] Dr. Murad? Dr. Murad, do you read me?
Yes. I've successfully accessed the console through the infrared port after several attempts.
Hurry up and get those defenses offline!
A lot quicker if I can focus on the task - there's a ton of data to look around!
Just find the master control and plug it off.
Dr. Murad? Come in, doctor.
The Militia is deploying more of their 'Mechs!
[static] Got it![static]
I have full access to the Association mainframes through the backdoor.
The Militia base is ours.
Not for long. Tech Barba and his people have already zipped through us.
We reached the inside and we'll start disarming the Militia members. Well done.
And now it's time to collect our pay. Good luck from here.
All those BattleMechs are Star League grade and the Militia seems to have quite a supply of them! There are more incoming!
Commander, you need to get me to the entrance of the facility. Otherwise it will be impossible to stop those 'Mechs from coming off the elevators.
